Here is the true value proposition of the AI Assistant, built around those 20-25 days of leave.

The Facts: Our employees have 20-25 days of leave. With 135,000 employees, this means on any given day, over 10,000 AT&T employees are "Out of Office."
The "Old Way": When a key engineer or project lead goes on vacation, the project stalls. Work piles up, deadlines are missed, and we create a single-point-of-failure. The manager scrambles, colleagues are burdened, and the sometime the team returns to a crisis.
The Fallacy: We've accepted this as a normal "cost of doing business." It is not. It is a critical, unmitigated risk.
2. The Solution: "Autonomous Operations"
This is where the AI Assistant becomes revolutionary.
When an engineer's leave is approved, their "AI Assistant" autonomously activates.
It doesn't just plan the work; it does the work. It handles their critical tasks, manages their queues, and resolves standard issues while they are gone.
We are no longer "covering" for the employee. We are enabling true Operational Continuity. The AI Assistant is the insurance policy against project delays.
